article.description: Sam Sessoms had 25 points as Binghamton narrowly beat Stony Brook 83-79 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Sessoms scores 25 points; Binghamton edges Stony Brook 83-79
article.linkText: Sessoms scores 25 points; Binghamton edges Stony Brook 83-79
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Sam Sessoms had 25 points as Binghamton narrowly beat Stony Brook 83-79 on Wednesday night. Pierre Sarr had 19 points, 14 rebounds and five assists for Binghamton (8-11, 2-4 America East Conference), which snapped its five-game road losing streak. George Tinsley added 14 points. Richard Caldwell Jr. had 14 points. Elijah Olaniyi had 20 points and six rebounds for the Seawolves (13-8, 4-2). Mouhamadou Gueye added 16 points and 10 rebounds. Andrew Garcia had 16 points. Makale Foreman, the Seawolves' second leading scorer coming into the matchup at 16 points per game, shot only 20 percent in the game (3 of 15). Binghamton plays New Hampshire at home on Saturday. Stony Brook faces UMass Lowell on the road next Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
